The paper deals with neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of linearized parses and attention mechanisms also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the WMT17 English-German task, which involves large-scale machine translation, indicating a possible connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) for handling complex input data.
